cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with statistical modeling of photographic images. The use of linear filters and their optimization for sparsity also suggests information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The potential applications of the proposed representation in denoising, compression, and texture representation indicate multimedia (cs.MM) as another likely sub-category. Finally, the mention of hierarchical decompositions suggests neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) as a possible sub-category.
